            "id": "83322c0774af4508bf7bf",
            "questionText": "Consider a newly discovered planet, Kepler-186f-b, which has a mass ($!$M$!$) of 5 times the Earth's mass ($!$M_E = 5.972 \\times 10^{24}$!$ kg) and a radius ($!$R$!$) of 1.5 times the Earth's radius ($!$R_E = 6.371 \\times 10^6$!$ m). A spacecraft of mass ($!$m = 1000$!$ kg) is launched from the surface of Kepler-186f-b. What is the minimum speed ($!$v$!$) with which the spacecraft must be launched from the surface of Kepler-186f-b to escape the planet's gravitational field?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "8b4c0c6d45da4034b65ce",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula required to calculate the escape speed from a gravitational field. Please select the formula that relates escape speed to the gravitational constant, the mass of the planet, and its radius.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "46604101-3be5-4092-ac9f-5c58ea2f77f3"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\sqrt{\\frac{GM}{R}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\sqrt{\\frac{GM}{R^2}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\sqrt{\\frac{2GM}{R}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\sqrt{\\frac{G2M}{R}}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "dc1e414cec10449ca76ed",
                    "stepText": "Now, calculate the mass of Kepler-186f-b knowing it is 5 times the Earth's mass. (Recall that Earth's mass is $!$5.972\\times10^{24}$!$ kg.) What is the mass of the planet?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "2.986e25"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "kg",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "670a8f569d1a48fe815fc",
                    "stepText": "Next, determine the radius of Kepler-186f-b given that it is 1.5 times the Earth's radius (Earth\u2019s radius is $!$6.371\\times10^{6}$!$ m). What is the planet's radius?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "9.5565e6"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "8c62135bbef24b60b28cc",
                    "stepText": "Using the computed mass and the gravitational constant $!$G = 6.67\\times10^{-11}$!$ m$!$^3$/kg/s$!$^2$!$, calculate the intermediate value by multiplying $!$2G$!$ with the mass and then dividing by the planet's radius. What is the value obtained inside the square root?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "4.17e8"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m^2/s^2",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "46604101-3be5-4092-ac9f-5c58ea2f77f3"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "3a13e3fbb96a4091833d6",
                    "stepText": "Finally, take the square root of the value from the previous step to determine the escape speed of the spacecraft. What is the minimum escape speed required?",
